# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __neg__, __pos__, __abs__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# decimal.Decimal defines all three unary arithmetic operators: true/true/true.
# This reflects Decimal's status as a complete IEEE 754 numeric type: -d flips
# the sign, +d canonicalizes the value, abs(d) returns the magnitude. All other
# decimal classes (Context, DecimalException, InvalidOperation, Overflow,
# Underflow) define none of the three operators: false for all 15 remaining rows.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table dc3346.combined:
